Kendall is a yoga teacher and yoga therapist in training based in San Diego, CA. She specializes in therapeutic yoga with an emphasis on stress relief and injury recovery. Enjoy her gentle guided meditations and relaxation practices here!

200 Hour Yoga Teacher Training (2016)

She has a BS degree focused on Exercise Physiology & Nutrition, is a RYT & a Strength and Conditioning Specialist. Kathleen empowers people to find their voices and express themselves, so they can live their truth with clarity and confidence. She teaches yoga, meditation, and movement in Chicago and online.

What I love to share are practices that connect us to our raw humanness, blending intention & intuition, traditional & modern influences, mixed with sweat and community. I love to weave in stories of Ganesha and Shiva. A particular breath that lights it up or slows it down. Postures accessible to all levels. Sometimes an external sigh, other times a mantra to traverse any mental spin. A hand gesture or full body mudra to focus our attention. Connected bhakti and pop tunes to lift our mood. Strengthening and lengthening our physical and energetic being.

I am deeply humbled by the gifts offered to me by my teachers and this practice. I have logged more than 20,000 Yoga Alliance hours as a student from a range of teachers from Vinyasa, Anusara, and Iyengar to Ayurveda, Bhakti, Tantra, and Shadow Yoga disciplines, and have been teaching for 20+ years. It is my life’s work to offer these teachings and to honor what has come before me with all the integrity I have....read more

Now it’s time for Karen to guide others who may be seeking the same!
